    Risk Assessment: Ability to identify and assess potential security risks and vulnerabilities within an organization's systems, networks, and processes.:Risk Management
    Risk Mitigation Strategies: Proficiency in developing and implementing risk mitigation strategies and controls to reduce the impact and likelihood of identified risks.:Risk Management
    Security Awareness and Training: Skills in developing and delivering security awareness and training programs to educate employees and stakeholders about security risks and best practices.:Risk Management
    Security Controls Assessment: Knowledge of security control frameworks (e.g., CIS Controls, NIST SP 800-53) and the ability to assess the effectiveness of implemented controls.:Risk Management
    Security Frameworks and Standards: Familiarity with industry security frameworks and standards, such as ISO 27001, NIST Cybersecurity Framework, and COBIT, and the ability to apply them to risk management processes.:Risk Management
    Security Metrics and Reporting: Proficiency in defining and tracking security metrics to measure the effectiveness of risk management efforts and provide meaningful reports to stakeholders.:Risk Management
    Stakeholder Management: Strong communication and interpersonal skills to engage with executives, board members, and other stakeholders, and effectively communicate risk-related information and recommendations.:Risk Management
    Strategic Thinking: Ability to think strategically and align cybersecurity risk management efforts with organizational goals and objectives.:Risk Management
    Threat Intelligence Analysis: Understanding of threat intelligence sources and the ability to analyze and interpret threat intelligence data to identify emerging risks and potential threats.:Risk Management
    Vendor and Third-Party Risk Management: Understanding of assessing and managing security risks associated with third-party vendors and conducting thorough vendor assessments.:Risk Management
